Our investigation is primarily concerned with the variation in the optoelectronic properties of the n-µc-SiO:H layer, therefore, the CO2 flow rate was altered to prepare different n-type layers. Investigation on the individual n-µc-SiO:H layers and their application in solar cells was conducted separately. In order to analyze their optoelectronic and structural properties, n-µc-SiO:H films were deposited on glass substrates. We used Raman spectral analysis to estimate the crystalline volume fraction (Xc); the following relation (1) was used to estimate Xc.1Xc=(I510+I500)/(I510+I500+I480)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
